metadata.name: The Great Reload
metadata.description:
Revolution comes with evolution,  
but we're stuck in an institution, 
chained from change,  
like the so-called free range,  
you're just another headless chicken,  
waiting for happiness to kick in,  
while the sick get sicker,  
the rich guy's wallet grows thicker,  
like someone hacked the hierarchy,  
because they didn't want you free,  
everything becomes streamlined,  
you don't even know you're blind,  
comfort in left and right opinions,  
it's all just dominion,  
upkeeping the status quo,  
he who refuses to leave can't grow,  
can't you hear nature calling?  
she finds our behaviors appalling,  
her fury forms destruction,  
volcanic anger throws an eruption,  
from the ashes a chance to rise,  
after demise we shall revise,  
with a fresh start at last,  
new technologies show in the forecast,  
a time to write our own code,  
it'll be the era of The Great Reload,
